Description: Creates a torus by sweeping a circular profile along a circular path (profile rotated 90Â° to meet sweep requirements).
Author: Tim Olson
Date: 2025-09-06
Notes: Save as .ppm and load via the Parametric Parts palette. Parameters in millimeters.

// Units
Units(1[mm]);
Input();

// Parameters
TubeR = Parameter("Tube Radius", 10, LINEAR, Interval(0.1, 10000)); // minor radius
TorusR = Parameter("Torus Radius", 20, LINEAR, Interval(0.1, 100000)); // major (path) radius

// Build profile (circle) and rotate it so its plane is perpendicular to the path plane
// Also offset the profile center along X by TorusR + TubeR
Profile2D = Circle(TubeR, TorusR + TubeR, 0); // lies in XY at the correct offset
Profile = RotateX(Profile2D, 90); // move profile into XZ plane

// Build path (circle) in XY plane
Path = Circle(TorusR, 0, 0);

// Sweep to form torus
Torus = Sweep(Profile, Path);

// Output
Output(Torus);
